rspektive. Dabei werden zum einen die fruchtbaren Wechselwirkungen zwischen Tillich und seinem akademischen Umfeld im Blick auf die Genese einer genuin 'kritischen Theologie' deutlich; zugleich entsteht ein konturschärferes Bild der geistigen Situation der Frankfurter Universität unmittelbar vor der nationalsozialistischen Machtübernahme.  aThis volume examines the multifaceted origins of Paul Tillich’s “critical theology” during the Frankfurt years (1929–1933) from the perspectives of source and reception history. In this way, it provides a compelling picture of the rich interactions between Tillich and his academic environment as well as the spiritual situation at the University of Frankfurt just before the National Socialist takeover.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aKulturtheologie. 4aReligionsphilosophie. 4aTillich, Paul. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aFrankfurt am Main.  aPhilosophy of Religion.  aTheology of Culture.  aTillich, Paul.1 aBrittain, Christopher Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFehige, Yiftach, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeimbrock, Hans-Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinde, Gesche, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoxter, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchreiber, Gerhard , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchreiber, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchulz, Heiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchulz, Heiko, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov